This charting example extends node-red-dashboard and the work by Colin Law here:
http://flows.nodered.org/flow/c3dc75c47323a2754f5285225bce64b5

View the chart at http://localhost:1880/ui

Both the dashboard chart and Colin's example uses time as the X-axis. The example
here uses an integer as the x-axis. Colin's example uses Chart.js inside a
node-red-dashboard template node. The example here leaves Colin's code almost 
unchanged except that the chart.js XAxis is changed from:

                xAxes: [{
                    type: 'time',
                    time: {
                        unit: 'minute',
                        unitStepSize: 1,
                        displayFormats: {
                            minute: 'HH:mm'
                        }
                    }
                }],

to this:
              xAxes: [{
                    type: 'linear',
                    position: 'bottom'
                    }
                ],

I also adjusted the way the nodes are rendered.

This example pre-prepares the data object and uses the msg.action = "load" 
method to ask the template code to render the data. 

A dashboard button on the UI page generates fresh data with a different 
scale each time.

